clubs.  &QL; 
2. NY YankeesCan the Yanks live while the Mets grab all the
headlines?  &QL; 
3. ClevelandAce in the making?  &UR; Bartolo Colon is 8-1 with a 2.42
ERA since the break.  &QL; 
4. TexasRangers are 36-4 when they score at least four runs in an
inning.  &QL; 
5. NY MetsFighting? Must be a New York thing we just wouldn't
understand.  &QL; 
6. HoustonAstros entered the weekend 28-19 since  &UR; Larry Dierker's
return.  &QL; 
7. ArizonaThat once comfortable lead seems to be dwindling by the
day.  &QL; 
8. CincinnatiStarting pitching has been exposed lately. Do Reds
have enough?  &QL; 
9. Boston &UR; Martinez got hammered Thursday.  &UR; Ramon, that is,
not &UR; Pedro.
 &UR; BOTTOM OF THE ORDER &QL; 
 &QL; 
30. Chicago CubsThe 24 August losses tied the club record for
futility in any month.  &QL; 
29. AnaheimThis has none of the trappings of a feel-good Disney
production.  &QL; 
28. Kansas CityManager  &UR; Tony Muser summed it up: ``Our offense is
just anemic.''  &QL; 
27. FloridaThe auditions for 2000 jobs have begun in earnest in
south Florida.  &QL; 
26. DetroitGM  &UR; Randy Smith is doing nothing but poring over the
free agents.  &QL; 
