<HEADLINE>
10 THINGS TO WATCH FOR THIS SEASON 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; 1. The Broncos, trying to become the first team to win three
consecutive Super Bowl titles, will wrap up the AFC West crown by
Halloween, Thanksgiving or Christmas? &QL; 
 &UR; 2. The NFL's richest owner, Paul Allen of the Seattle Seahawks,
didn't make Mike Holmgren the NFL's wealthiest coach to extend the
league's longest playoff drought. The Seahawks will reach the
playoffs for the first time since 1988. &QL; 
 &UR; 5. The league's best coach, Bill Parcells of the New York Jets, has
one more magic trick up his sleeve before he retires: Find a way to
get the all-time goat of the Fiesta Bowl, quarterback Vinny
Testaverde, to lead the Jets to the Super Bowl. &QL; 
 &UR; 3. Name the team that won't get at least 100 yards rushing against
the Cardinals. Sorry, the Amsterdam Admirals aren't on this year's
schedule. &QL; 
 &UR; 4. The first NFL coach fired will be a) Bruce Coslet, b) Bobby
Ross, c) Pete Carroll, d) Norv Turner? &QL; 
 &UR; 6. Oakland Raiders owner Al Davis will try to move the team back to
Los Angeles before the league puts an expansion team there. &QL; 
 &UR; 7. New Orleans Saints Coach Mike Ditka, who traded most of his
franchise for the rights to Heisman Trophy winner Ricky Williams,
will blow his top after the rookie running back goes on injured
reserve because of a recurring ankle injury. &QL; 
 &UR; 8. Ditka, upset by a loss to NFC West-rival San Francisco, vows
never, ever, ever to coach again. &QL; 
 &UR; 9. With so many running backs and so few wide receivers, Miami
Coach Jimmy Johnson will consider installing the wishbone offense. &QL; 
 &UR; 10. The crazed fans of the expansion Browns won't care if the team
wins even five games as long as one is against owner Art Modell's
Baltimore Ravens. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-05-99 0136EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
