Wadsworth, DT Eric Swann, WR Rob Moore, WR Frank Sanders, DE Simeon
Rice, CB Aeneas Williams, LB Ron McKinnon. &QL; 
 &UR; GONE TO EVIL FORCES: LB Jamir Miller, OT Lomas Brown, FB Larry
Centers. &QL; 
 &UR; TEST OF WILL: The team plays three of its first four on the road in
an upgraded schedule that is ranked the fourth toughest in the
league. Compounding the difficulty is a rash of injuries and
holdouts that will put it well into the second month before it hits
its stride. It must weather that storm. &QL; 
 &UR; WILL PREVAIL IF: The Cardinals ever get their full team onto the
field signed and healthy. &QL; 
 &UR; WILL PERISH IF: The run-stopping doesn't improve and QB Plummer
does not shake his tendency to start games slowly and make killer
turnovers. &QL; 
 &UR; CYBERSPACE HOME: www.azcardinals.com. &QL; 
 &UR; 3. New York Giants &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; 1998 ISSUE: 8-8, third. &QL; 
 &UR; FEARLESS LEADER: Jim Fassel (18-14-1). &QL; 
 &UR; HALL OF JUSTICE: Giants Stadium (79,593). &QL; 
 &UR; THE NEW AVENGERS: Free agent QB Kerry Collins; rookies OL Luke
Petitgout, RB Joe Montgomery. &QL; 
 &UR; STILL A GOOD  &UR; GUY: OT Roman Oben, DE Michael Strahan, LB Jessie
Armstead. &QL; 
 &UR; GONE TO EVIL FORCES: G Greg Bishop, DE Chad Bratzke, WR Chris
Calloway, S Tito Wooten. &QL; 
 &UR; TEST OF WILL: The divisional foes are the Giants' stoutest test in
a schedule that, based on 1998 records, is among the league's five
easiest. That comes after the Giants were crushed last season by a
killer schedule. &QL; 
 &UR; WILL PREVAIL IF: The QB controversy reaches a favorable conclusion,
the wide receivers are the real deal, and the defense can withstand
the loss of Chad Bratzke. &QL; 
 &UR; WILL PERISH IF: The average running backs play below average and
the secondary doesn't get torched. &QL; 
 &UR; CYBERSPACE HOME: www.giants.com. &QL; 
 &UR; 4. Washington Redskins &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; 1998 ISSUE: 6-10, fourth, NFC East. &QL; 
 &UR; FEARLESS LEADER: Norv Turner (32-47-). &QL; 
 &UR; HALL OF JUSTICE: Jack Kent Cooke Stadium (80,116). &QL; 
 &UR; THE NEW AVENGERS: Free agents QB Brad Johnson, QB Rodney Peete, LB
Fred Strickland, DE Marco Coleman, FB Larry Centers, WR Irving
Fryar; rookie CB Champ Bailey. &QL; 
 &UR; STILL A GOOD  &UR; GUY: WR Michael Westbrook, OT Tre Johnson, RB Skip
Hicks, CB Darrell Green, DT Dana Stubblefield, DT Dan Wilkinson. &QL; 
 &UR; GONE TO EVIL FORCES: QB Trent Green, WR Leslie Shepherd, RB Terry
Allen, TE Jamie Asher, LB Marvcus Patton, LB Ken Harvey, CB Cris
Dishman. &QL; 
 &UR; TEST OF WILL: One of the league's softest schedules awaits the
Redskins as Coach Norv Turner retools his offense and tries to save
his job. Rookie CB Champ Bailey should help a defense that twice
was shredded by the Cardinals. &QL; 
 &UR; WILL PREVAIL IF: The league's 28th-ranked defense figures a way to
stop a foe and one of the new quarterbacks takes control. &QL; 
 &UR; WILL PERISH IF: It's business as usual in stopping the rush, where
the Skins were among the worst. &QL; 
 &UR; CYBERSPACE HOME: www.redskins.com. &QL; 
 &UR; 5. Philadelphia Eagles &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; 1998 ISSUE: 3-13, fifth. &QL; 
 &UR; FEARLESS LEADER: Andy Reid (first season). &QL; 
 &UR; HALL OF JUSTICE: Veterans Stadium (65,352). &QL; 
 &UR; THE NEW AVENGERS: Free agents RB Eric Bienemy, TE Jamie Asher, DT
Mark Wheeler; rookie QB Donovan McNabb. &QL; 
 &UR; STILL A GOOD  &UR; GUY: OT Tra Thomas, RB Duce Staley, DE Hugh Douglas,
CB Bobby Taylor. &QL; 
 &UR; GONE TO EVIL FORCES: RB Charlie Garner, WR Irving Fryar, QB Bobby
Hoying, QB Rodney Peete. &QL; 
 &UR; TEST OF WILL: Reid and Co. will be tested coming out of the gate
with an opening eight games that include the Cardinals, Tampa Bay,
Buffalo, two against the New York Giants, Dallas and Miami. The
easy game in the first half of the season is against Chicago _ but
it's on the road in Week 7. &QL; 
 &UR; WILL PREVAIL IF: The team is quick to pick up Reid's new system and
the defense steps up and creates turnovers. &QL; 
 &UR; WILL PERISH IF: Rookie QB Donovan McNabb stumbles out of the gate
against a tough schedule. &QL; 
 &UR; CYBERSPACE HOME: www.eaglesnet.com. &QL;
</P>
