<P>
   ESPN-ANNIVERSARY (BRISTOL, Conn.) _ Ten weeks ago, when Tony
Hawk turned the first ``900'' in a skateboardng competition, it was
not only fitting that ESPN be there to record the event, it was
pretty much required, dude. Hawk was competing, after all, in the X
(for extreme) Games, an invention of ESPN, which 20 years ago
launched itself into the cable consciousness with these words from
sportscaster Lee Leonard: ``If you're a fan, if you're a fan, what
you'll see in the next minutes, hours and days to follow may
convince you you've gone to sports heaven.''
</P>
