<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sept. 6 and thereafter. For questions about stories, please contact
Stewart Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   LA-LABOR-TOWN (Los Angeles) _ Los Angeles has never been known
as a labor city like New York, Chicago or San Francisco. In fact,
its history is marked with anti-labor sentiment. Yet, as the nation
commemorates Labor Day on Monday, nowhere else will the celebration
be louder than in Los Angeles, where recent gains have made it one
of the most active union cities in the country. By Rick Orlov and
Beth Barrett. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California
news files.)
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-BOX-OFFICE (Los Angeles) _ ``The Sixth Sense'' continued
its supernatural late-summer performance at the nation's
multiplexes, easily posting its fifth consecutive victory with an
impressive $21 million at 2,775 theaters for Friday-Sunday amid a
moderate Labor Day weekend overall at the box office, studio
sources said Sunday. By Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
